<TITLE> Mamun gets bail in Niko case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar18 (bdnews24.com)  Controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun secured Wednesday a two-month interim bail from the High Court in Niko corruption case. The bench of justices Syed A B Mahmudul Haque and Mainul Islam Chowdhury also asked the government to explain why he would not get permanent bail. Assistant director of Anticorruption Commission Md Mahbubul Alam filed the case on Dec 8, 2007 with Tejgaon Police Station. Charges were pressed in the trial court on May 5, 2009. Mamun, former prime minister Khaleda Zia's elder son Tarique Rahman's close friend and business associate, was accused of causing nearly Tk 14000 crore in state losses through closing the oil and gas exploration agreement with the Canadian firm Niko Resources
